longBusinessSummary: Grupo TraxiÃ³n, S.A.B. de C.V. operates as a transportation and logistics company in Mexico. The company offers dry van, refrigerated trailer, hopper trailer, platform, thorton, intermodal and multimodal, import and export, national distribution, cross border, port, cross dock, and door-to-door freight services; logistics integration services, such as ground, control tower, networks consultancy, consolidated, and specialized services, as well as land, air, and sea administration services; and warehousing services, including dedicated storage, shared warehouse, cross-dock, inventory management, inbound and outbound, finished goods and raw materials, bonded warehouse, export shipments, reverse logistic, automated sorter picking, radiofrequency and voice-picking, and co-packing and value-added services. It also provides warehouse management, transport management, yard management, and control tower systems; messaging and packaging, pickup and delivery option, document return, tracking, national and international shipment, guarantees and shipping insurance, and preparation services; and personnel and student transportation services, as well as passengers transportation services. In addition, the company offers rental services of buses and vans for corporate events, tourism, and special events; and moving and advertising services. It provides its services under the LIPU, Transportadora Egoba, MyM, Grupo SID, Auto Express Frontera Norte, Publica Advertising, REDPACK, Autotransportes El Bisonte, Traxi, TraxiÃ³n Logistics, and Traxporta names. The company was formerly known as Fondo de Transporte MÃ©xico, S.A.P.I. de C.V. and changed its name to Grupo TraxiÃ³n, S.A.B. de C.V. in September 2017. Grupo TraxiÃ³n, S.A.B. de C.V. was incorporated in 2011 is based in Mexico City, Mexico.
